{
  "doc_id": "44054",
  "text": "In addition, it is known that macrophages are important APCs. It was demonstrate that these cells can contribute to innate immunity employing various cytokines and chemokines [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, it was not possible to evaluate macrophages in the present study. It was demonstrated that responses of the macrophages and DCs in the production of cytokines and chemokines were similar for the various microbial challenges [CITATION_3] . Huang et al. [CITATION_4] demonstrated that only response of immature DC to polymicrobial challenge could contribute to production of IL-6 [CITATION_5] . Furthermore, others studies are necessary to understand mechanisms that affect the relation between immature DCs and IL-6.",
